  "prompt": "Will operating systems in the future support Braille displays?",
  "response": "Yes, it is highly likely that future operating systems will continue to support Braille displays and potentially improve their integration. Accessibility technologies, including Braille support, have been gaining more attention and advancements over recent years. Operating systems such as Windows, macOS, and various Linux distributions already provide substantial support for Braille displays, and ongoing efforts by technology companies aim to make digital environments more inclusive for users with visual impairments.\n\nWith the increasing emphasis on inclusivity and accessibility, future developments in operating systems are expected to enhance compatibility with Braille displays, offering improved features, easier setup processes, and better user experiences. Additionally, advancements in machine learning and artificial intelligence might lead to more innovative and efficient ways to use Braille technology, further empowering users who rely on these devices.",
